./CHANGELOG.md:19:- Added depth-2 EMSD performance adjustment report helpers (frac-0027): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/emsd_performance.py` now exposes frozen `PerformanceEventSpec`, `PerformanceEventSnapshot`, and `PerformanceAdjustmentReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `amp_pressure_band`, `release_shape_band`, `brightness_shape_band`, `space_amount_band`, `build_performance_event_snapshot`, `build_performance_adjustment_report`, and `summarize_performance_adjustment_report` so diagnostics callers can resolve the existing live `render_adjustments_for_event(...)` path into operator-readable per-event and batch summaries. Existing `PerformanceAdjustments` fields and note-level playback behavior are preserved; `tests/test_emsd_performance_depth.py` pins band cutpoints, snapshot/live-adjustment parity, ordered aggregate role/voice/DSP/sample metadata, empty-sequence rejection, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end Theramini ducking and DSP propagation, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_emsd_performance.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
./CHANGELOG.md:21:- Added depth-2 EMSD runtime snapshot/report helpers (frac-0026): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/emsd_runtime.py` now exposes `CANONICAL_ARC_PHASES`, `CANONICAL_DENSITY_BANDS`, frozen `EMSDPhaseSnapshot` and `EMSDRuntimeReport` dataclasses, plus pure helpers `arc_phase_index`, `arc_phase_band`, `density_pressure_band`, `build_phase_snapshot`, `build_runtime_report`, and `summarize_runtime_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can resolve a live `EMSDLiveContext` into operator-readable phase diagnostics (arc phase + index + opening/dialogue/resolution band, family/patch/sample-source identity, arc density target, max active roles, mix LUFS, density bias + calm/neutral/intense pressure band, and artistic identity statement), aggregate a sequence of snapshots into a typed runtime report (ordered phase history, canonical phase counts including zeros, canonical density-band counts, ordered distinct families/patches/sample sources, ordered arc-phase transition pairs, mean/max/min density bias rounded to 4 decimals), and emit a JSON-safe summary mirroring those fields. Existing `EMSDLiveContext` fields, `build_live_emsd_context(...)`, and `composer_emsd_extras(...)` semantics are preserved so EMSD/composer/Theramini integration tests are unaffected; `tests/test_emsd_runtime_depth.py` pins canonical arc-phase ordering, opening/dialogue/resolution band mapping (with `"unclassified"` fallback for unknown phases), density-band cutpoints, snapshot field resolution, multi-snapshot trajectory shape, JSON round-trip stability, end-to-end snapshot/context phase agreement, empty-sequence rejection, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_emsd_runtime.py`, `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors (the smoke test for the narrative HTTP `/healthz` + `/readyz` + bearer-token hardening surface).
./CHANGELOG.md:23:- Added depth-2 motif-lifecycle report helpers (frac-0025): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/motif_lifecycle.py` now exposes frozen `MotifLifecycleStep` and `MotifLifecycleReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lifecycle_state_index`, `build_lifecycle_step`, `canonical_lifecycle_path`, `build_lifecycle_report`, and `summarize_lifecycle_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can advance a motif through the one canonical lifecycle path and emit a JSON-safe operator summary with ordered history, current/terminal state, valid next states, canonical state counts, contour/rhythm/material deltas, and per-step state-band/material diagnostics. Existing transition rules, deterministic transformations, `advance(...)`, `MotifLifecycleManager`, and repertoire-shape recall behavior are preserved; `tests/test_motif_lifecycle_depth.py` pins the new report surface, manager end-to-end agreement, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_motif_lifecycle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
./CHANGELOG.md:25:- Added depth-2 score-tree report helpers (frac-0024): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py` now exposes frozen `ScoreTreeSectionReport` and `ScoreTreeReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `motif_lifecycle_band`, `section_phrase_load_band`, `count_motif_lifecycle_states`, `build_score_tree_section_report`, `build_score_tree_report`, and `summarize_score_tree_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can resolve a `ScoreTree` into operator-readable shape diagnostics — per-section view (id, scene, function, harmonic role/function, cadence, groove, transition intent, transform strength, target duration, phrase count, named phrase-load band, ordered de-duplicated motif refs across the section's phrases, and a `production_course_complete` flag against `PRODUCTION_COURSE_KEYS`) and tree-level view (piece id, title, form family/class/composition mode, ending family, planned duration, section/motif/phrase counts, ordered `motif_lifecycle_counts` covering every `MOTIF_LIFECYCLE_STATES` entry with zeros for absent states, ordered tuple of unreferenced motif ids, and per-section reports) — and emit a JSON-safe summary mirroring those fields. Existing `MOTIF_LIFECYCLE_STATES`, `PRODUCTION_COURSE_KEYS`, `MotifNode`, `PhraseNode`, `SectionNode`, and `ScoreTree.to_dict` / `to_json` / `from_dict` / `minimal` semantics are preserved so the JSON round-trip and minimal-tree behavior continue unchanged; `tests/test_score_tree_depth.py` pins lifecycle-band mapping (with `"unclassified"` fallback for unknown states), phrase-load band cutpoints, canonical-only lifecycle counting, populated-tree section/tree shape, JSON round-trip stability, minimal-tree zero-state handling, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_score_tree.py` and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` remain regression anchors (the latter for the narrative HTTP `/healthz` + `/readyz` + bearer-token hardening surface).
./CHANGELOG.md:27:- Added depth-2 sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0023): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan` so diagnostics and composer callers can inspect a concrete `sw_sampler` dispatch before or after buffer loading. The plan reports sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and the canonical `/s_new` synth argument pairs; live `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` helper, preserving existing OSC ordering and lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins named density bands, loaded/unloaded plan output, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
./CHANGELOG.md:29:- Added depth-2 sample-lab report helpers (frac-0022): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_lab.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplePlanReport` dataclass plus pure helpers `density_band`, `threshold_band`, `intensity_band`, `build_sample_plan_report`, and `summarize_sample_plan_report` so EMSD operator/diagnostics callers can resolve a `SamplePlan` together with its `sample_bank` freshness and fallback rule into one operator-readable view (source identity and capture path, refresh and freshness seconds, fallback list, cadence state, section function, transforms tuple plus count, density and named density band, buffer seconds, trigger threshold and named threshold band, intensity and named intensity band, and study focus) and emit a stable JSON-safe summary. Existing `SAMPLE_SOURCES`, `SAMPLE_SOURCE_ALIASES`, `SAMPLE_FALLBACKS`, `canonical_sample_source_name`, `sample_source`, `sample_bank`, and `plan_environmental_sampling` semantics are preserved (cadence and section-function shaping unchanged); `SamplePlan` now also carries the resolved `cadence_state` so reports can be built without re-passing it. `tests/test_sample_lab_depth.py` pins the band cutpoints, plan/bank field mirroring, alias-to-canonical bank resolution, section-function carry-through, JSON-safe summary shape, end-to-end downstream use, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sample_lab.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
./CHANGELOG.md:31:- Added depth-2 rollout control report helpers (frac-0021): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/rollout_controls.py` now exposes frozen `RolloutFlagState` and `RolloutControlReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `flag_state`, `rollout_control_report`, and `summarize_rollout_controls` so operator/status callers can inspect the resolved SenseWeave rollout flags, raw environment values, default/defaulted/env source, enabled/disabled counts, and effective self-critique state without changing existing flag defaults. Existing `SenseWeaveFeatureFlags`, `load_feature_flags`, and downstream practice-curriculum, self-critique, and piece-commission behavior are preserved; `tests/test_rollout_controls.py` pins the new report surface, downstream end-to-end use, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_senseweave_rollout_controls.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
./CHANGELOG.md:33:- Added depth-2 silence budget report helpers (frac-0020): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/silence_budget.py` now exposes frozen `LaneSilenceBudgetStat` and `SilenceBudgetReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_silence_budget_stat`, `analyze_silence_budget`, and `summarize_silence_budget_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R10 rule once and inspect per-lane phrase outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, original phrase count, breath-extension count, tacet step count, distinct tacet phrase count, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TARGET_DENSITY`, `DEFAULT_THRESHOLD`, `SilenceBudgetRule.apply`, and `apply_silence_budget` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_silence_budget_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_silence_budget_depth.py` pins tacet-trigger lane shaping, breath-extension lane shaping, non-melodic non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
