 ## Unreleased
 
+- Added depth-2 Tamagotchi diagnostics (frac-0035): `my-claw/tools/tamagotchi.py` now exposes frozen `PetVitalSnapshot` and `PetFleetReport` dataclasses plus typed helpers `pet_health_band`, `pet_activity_band`, `xp_to_next_stage`, `stage_progress_fraction`, `pet_attention_reasons`, `build_pet_vital_snapshot`, `build_pet_fleet_report`, and `summarize_pet_fleet_report`. Existing JSON persistence, task XP, idle decay, and GlyphWeave display contracts are preserved, while `PetManager.fleet_report()` now gives status/diagnostic callers an end-to-end health/activity/fleet summary with canonical pet ordering, aggregate XP/tasks, mean vitals, active/sleeping/attention agents, and XP leader. `tests/test_tamagotchi_depth.py` pins helper bands, frozen snapshot/report shape, JSON-safe summaries, persistence round-trip, and fractal depth >= 2; existing tamagotchi/GlyphWeave tests and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
+
 - Added depth-2 startle daemon processing (frac-0034): `my-claw/tools/startle_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `read_room_activity`, `amp_from_room`, `update_baseline`, `baseline_value`, `render_output`, `write_output`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus a `DaemonState` dataclass that combines the existing `senseweave.startle.StartleState` with a rolling-baseline tracker. The daemon now reads `/tmp/room_activity.json`, takes the louder of `window_mic_amp` / `cypherclaw_mic_amp`, maintains a 20-sample rolling-median baseline (with a non-zero floor so the detector never sees a degenerate baseline), runs the existing `update_startle` rules, and atomically writes the consumer contract (`startled`, `startle_count`, `cooldown_active`, `face_reaction`, `should_mute`, `amp`, `baseline`, `timestamp`) consumed by `inner_life.world_model.poll_state`. Loop control gains `--once`, `--interval`, `--room-path`, `--state-path`, and `--max-iterations`; existing `senseweave.startle` rules are unchanged. `tests/test_startle_daemon.py` pins import safety, baseline/amp helpers, end-to-end loud-room startle output, and quiet-room loop output; `tests/test_startle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
 
 - Added depth-2 sensory journal daemon processing (frac-0033): `my-claw/tools/sensory_journal_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers for reading fused organism state, normalizing Theramini/room/mood snapshots, detecting ordered Theramini-start, room-transient, and energy-shift events, writing through the existing `senseweave.sensory_journal` JSONL contract, and running the loop with `max_iterations` / `--once` for tests and smoke runs. `tests/test_sensory_journal_daemon.py` pins import safety, meaningful event descriptions, one-cycle journal writes, and duplicate suppression across repeated active cycles; the existing sensory journal suite and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
